- `cells`, `liveSet`, `neighborCount`, `x`, `y`, `count`, `dx`, `dy`, `survivors`, `n`, `candidates`, `key`, `born`, `ax`, `ay`, `bx`, `by` = 17 bindings

Invocations (mass 2 each):
- `new Set(...)`, `cells.map(...)`, `liveSet.has(...)` (x2), `cells.filter(...)`, `neighborCount(x,y)` (x2), `candidates.add(...)`, `key.split(...)`, `.map(Number)`, `born.push(...)`, `born.sort(...)`, spread `[...survivors, ...born]` = ~13 invocations

Conditionals (mass 4 each):
- `if (dx === 0 && dy === 0) continue;` (x2), `if (liveSet.has(...)) count++`, `return n === 2 || n === 3`, `if (!liveSet.has(key))`, `if (neighborCount(x,y) === 3)`, `ax !== bx ? ax - bx : ay - by` = 7 conditionals

Loops (mass 5 each):
- `cells.map(...)` (1), `for dx` inside neighborCount (1), `for dy` inside neighborCount (1), `cells.filter(...)` (1), `for (const [x, y] of cells)` (1), `for dx` in candidates block (1), `for dy` in candidates block (1), `for (const key of candidates)` (1), `key.split(",").map(Number)` (1), `born.sort(...)` (1) = 10 loops

